nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Arginine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network prioritizes the literature-supported cyanosulfidic synthesis of an arginine alpha-aminonitrile precursor from HCN, acetylene, NH3, H2S, and cyanamide under Cu photoredox/UV conditions in surface geothermal settings, then converts that precursor to free arginine by hydrolysis. Hydrothermal chemistry is used conservatively and only where supported by the supplied research: vents provide H2, reduced carbon species, pyruvate, and alanine under Fe-S mineral catalysis, supplying connected feedstocks and environmental interconnection without overclaiming direct arginine assembly at high temperature. A secondary, explicitly downgraded route uses literature-supported post-synthetic guanidination of ornithine residues in peptides by cyanamide, followed by peptide hydrolysis to release arginine; this branch is included as a plausible systems-chemistry entry consistent with the reported ornithine-to-arginine transition but is not treated as the primary route. Ten distinct pathways are enumerated as different valid traversals through the connected network, with HCN, cyanamide, ornithine-containing peptide, arginine alpha-aminonitrile, and arginine as hub/convergence species.\n\nMOLECULES (23 nodes):\n  - mol_001: HCN (HCN) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_002: C2H2 (acetylene) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2CHCN (acrylonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: C3H6N2 (beta-aminopropionitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CH2N2 (cyanamide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C4H8N4 (guanidinated beta-aminopropionitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C4H9N3O (hemiaminal 37) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C5H9N4O (cyanohydrin intermediate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C5H11N4OS (alpha-hydrox