nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Arginine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network prioritizes the literature-supported cyanosulfidic synthesis of an arginine alpha-aminonitrile precursor from acetylene, HCN, NH3, H2S, cyanamide, and UV-driven Cu photoredox chemistry in shallow surface settings, then converts that precursor to free arginine by hydrolysis in prebiotic aqueous environments. Hydrothermal chemistry is used conservatively and literature-consistently to supply reduced feedstocks and shared hubs such as formate, acetate, pyruvate, ammonia, and sulfide under Fe-S mineral catalysis, which then feed surface photoredox chemistry. A secondary, explicitly downgraded route follows the reported abiotic guanidination of ornithine-containing peptides or free ornithine by cyanamide in aqueous solution, reflecting the literature view that arginine may have entered chemical evolution as a post-synthetic modification rather than as a primary free monomer. The ten pathways below are distinct traversals through one connected bipartite network and mostly converge on the best-supported arginine alpha-aminonitrile hub before final hydrolysis to arginine.\n\nMOLECULES (23 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: NH3 (ammonia) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formate/formic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: C2H4O2 (acetate/acetic acid) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C2H2 (acetylene) [starting]\n  - mol_010: CH2N2 (cyanamide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C3H3N (acrylonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C3H6N2 (beta-aminopropionitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C4H8N4 (guanidinated beta-aminopropionitrile) [hu